comments:
On 25.3.1885 the part in Leicestershire  
    became part of the parish of Stockerston, so that thereafter Stoke Dry was 
    entirely 
    in Rutland. See also Table 2, note (f).

On 25.3.1885 the part in Northamptonshire became part of the parish of Gretton, so that thereafter Thorpe by 
    Water was entirely in Rutland. See also Table 2, note (f).
